                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'd love to see instanced boss mobs.
<br />

<br />
Case in point: you and your guild work long and hard to get to a particular level in the game and because of the competition over a mob have little to no chance of seeing said mob.  This forces your members to move to guilds that work the hours those mobs are up, or suffer from not being able to get to them.  With instanced boss zones, this problem could be elliminated.
<br />

<br />
Now, we need to maintain rarity of drops and some level of competition should also be maintained.  Thus, the quests necessary to get to a top end boss instanced zone should be quite involved and difficult.  Further, the boss doesn't have to be up in the instanced zone... but, should have a decent chance of being up.  Finally, the rarity of drops can be maintained simply by regulating the frequency of certain drops.
<br />

<br />
Now, on the rarity of drops... nothing is more disenchanting then spending a lifetime in a zone hoping for a drop... only to see someone else come along and get the same drop in 5 minutes.  The frequency of the drops could be modified on a character basis.  Thus, someone hunting an epic drop could visit the zone and effectively be flagged if they kill the mob that drops the epic item... each visit to the zone (not each kill of the mob) would increase that flag and increase the chances of said drop.  After a number of visits, the drop should almost be guaranteed.  The number could be fairly large, say 100 visits, but, I'd think 30-ish would be more reasonable.
<br />

<br />
The point is to limit some of the unhealthy competition seen when going after top end mobs or quest mobs that are highly sought after.  Definetly maintain the difficulty of the quest, the rarity of the drops (within reason) but let's not have things be simply frustrating... give us the chance to see said mob and the knowledge that within a reasonable amount of time we will get that drop... and we can all progress IF we put in due diligence and skill.  Nothing is more dejecting than having a guild or several individuals block you because they can... or visiting a zone/boss for more than a year trying for a single drop.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />GnarliAnna
<br />
E65.60/CT h+ 1.807khp 4.01km ft8 G++&lt;3 e++(+++) o++ T+++(+++++) L+ H++(+++) f++ g b@ c++ t+++ D++ X++</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
