                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My question would be for on the boss mobs, how would it be known which item you are trying to obtain, as opposed to all others? Let's take the Emperor in Ssraeshza Temple for example, and you want the Koadic's Robe of Heightened Focus. How will this flagging procedure be able to pick out what item you want? What about the 30+ other people on your raid who all want a different arrangement of items to drop? There is really no possible way to make sure a certain item drops with a different percentage everytime a mob is killed, instead of another item in the mobs loot table. It just depends on your luck when killing the said mob. For you, the Koadic's Robe may seem rare, but for another guild, it may seem common.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=273350" target="_blank" class="postlink">Mistress Senilea Starbreeze</a>
<br />
65 Coercer of Bristlebane
